<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Typing Test Setup</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Bebas+Neue&family=Courier+Prime:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400;1,700&family=Source+Code+Pro:ital,wght@0,200..900;1,200..900&family=WDXL+Lubrifont+TC&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        html, body {
        height: 100%;
        margin: 0;
        }
        body {
            background: linear-gradient(to top, #7272ed, rgba(0,0,0,0.8));
            background-repeat: repeat-y;
            background-size: 100% auto;
            color:yellow
            }
        body::before {
            content: "";
            position: fixed;
            top: 0;
            left: 0;
            width: 100%;
            height: 100%;
            background: linear-gradient(to top, #7272ed, rgba(0,0,0,0.8));
            z-index: -1;
            }

        .Page1{
            height: 150vh;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: space-evenly;
            
            
        }
        
        
        .header-title{
            justify-self: center;
            margin-bottom: 5rem;
            font-size: 5rem;
            color: white
        }
        h2{
            justify-self: center;
            font-size: 4rem;
            font-family: "Courier New";        }

        .typing-text {
  overflow: hidden;
  color:yellow;
  font-family: 'Courier New';
  white-space: nowrap;
  width: 0;
  height: 11rem;
  font-size: 5rem;
  animation: 
    typeIn 3s steps(22) forwards;
  position: relative;
}

.i{
    font-style: italic;
font-family: "Source Code Pro", monospace;
  animation: ChangeFont 2.8s step-end infinite;
  animation-delay: 3s;
  animation-fill-mode: forwards;
  display: inline-block;
}

@keyframes typeIn {
  to {
    width: 22ch;
  }
}



@keyframes ChangeFont {
  0%{font-family: "Source Code Pro", monospace;}
  
  33%{  font-family: "Bebas Neue", sans-serif;
}
66%{  font-family: "WDXL Lubrifont TC", sans-serif;
}   
  
}
        .CardContainer{
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: row;
            height: 100%;
            align-items: flex-end;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            

        }

        .TextCard{
            border-radius: 1rem;
            border: black;
            padding: 2rem;
            margin: 2.5rem;
            width: 50%; 
            /* height: auto; */
           background-image: url('/assets/images/kb.jpg');
           background-repeat: no-repeat;
           overflow: wrap;
           justify-self: center;



        }
        
        .text-to-display {
            color:white;
            opacity: 0;
            transform: translateY(-20px);
            animation: headerEnter 0.8s ease forwards;
            color: white;
            background-color: rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
            font-size: 1.5rem;        

            }

            @keyframes headerEnter {
            to {
                opacity: 1;
                transform: translateY(0);
            }
        }

        form { max-width: 80vw; margin: auto; }
        label { display: block; margin-top: 20px; }
        select, button { width: 100%; padding: 8px; margin-top: 5px; border-radius: 1rem; height: 4rem; background: #f0d491}
        button{
        margin-top: 6rem;
        background: rgb(77,238,234);
        width: 30%;
        border: none;

        }
    </style>
</head>
<body >
    <div class="Page1">
    <h1 class="header-title">TypeFlow_</h1>
    <div class="typing-text">Speed is the new <div class="i">flex</div>_</div>

    <div class="CardContainer">
        <div class="TextCard">
            <div class="text-to-display" >
            In today’s fast-paced digital world, typing quickly and accurately is an essential skill that can unlock new productivity levels. TypeFlow is designed to help you improve your typing speed effortlessly while maintaining precision. Our sleek interface tracks your real-time progress, highlights errors instantly, and challenges you with varied text samples — from everyday phrases to complex passages. Whether you’re a beginner looking to build confidence or a professional aiming to sharpen your skills, TypeFlow adapts to your pace and keeps you motivated. Push your limits, track your improvement, and experience the flow of typing like never before. Fast. Smooth. Focused.
        </div>
        </div>
        </div>
    </div>
<div class="Page2">
    <h2 class="">SET UP YOUR TYPING TEST</h1>
    <form action="/typetest" method="POST">

        

        <label for="level">Level:</label>
        <select id="level" name="level" required>
            <option value="Beginner">Beginner</option>
            <option value="Intermediate">Intermediate</option>
            <option value="Advanced">Advanced</option>
            <option value="Pro">Pro</option>
        </select>

        <label for="time">Time:</label>
        <select id="time" name="time" required>
            <option value="30">30s</option>
            <option value="60">60s</option>
            <option value="120">120s</option>
            <option value="180">180s</option>
        </select>

        <label for="keys">Give Test only from the keys in:</label>
        <select id="keys" name="keys" required>
            <option value="Overall_keyboard">Overall Keyboard</option>
            <option value="Home_row">Home row</option>
            <option value="Top_row">Top Row</option>
            <option value="Bottom_row">Bottom Row</option>
            <option value="Punctuations_numbers">Punctuations and Numbers</option>
        </select>

        <label for="emphasis">Emphasis on:</label>
        <select id="emphasis" name="emphasis" required>
            <option value="Overall_keyboard">Overall Keyboard Equally</option>
            <option value="Home_row">Home row</option>
            <option value="Top_row">Top Row</option>
            <option value="Bottom_row">Bottom Row</option>
            <option value="Punctuations_numbers">Punctuations and Numbers</option>
        </select>
        
        <label for="random">Random or Readable Text?</label>
        <select id="random" name="random" required>
            <option value="RealLife">Readable</option>
            <option value="Random">Random</option>
        </select>

        <button type="submit" style="margin-top: 30px;">Start Test</button>
    </form>
    </div>

</body>
</html></select>